@pedroigor @mposolda I agree with the discussion here and the @pedroigor 's branch https://github.com/pedroigor/keycloak/tree/KEYCLOAK-12137.
Only I would like to mention is that we need to describe the assumption just below explicitly on keycloak's document.


AD must make sure the bearer token is secure in transit (TLS) and at rest (if they need to store it).
AD should have a high level of trust


@pedroigor If you do not have any plan to change your branch further drastically, I would like to pick up it and continue my work based on it. WDYT?

